-- Philippine Stocks: Benguet Slumps, PetroEnergy Resources Rises
-- B y   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 2012-05-30T04:31:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-30/benguet-pal-holdings-san-miguel-philippine-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon break in  Manila .  The  Philippine Stock Exchange Index (PCOMP)  fell 0.5 percent to
4,998.04. The measure is heading for a 3.9 percent loss this
month, the first monthly decline since November.  Benguet Corp. Class B shares  (BCB PM), which have no
ownership restrictions, fell 11 percent to 24 pesos, heading for
the sharpest loss since May 8. The company’s profit this year
may reach 1 billion pesos ($23 million), President Philip Romualdez said. Benguet made a profit of 1.39 billion pesos in
2011, a stock-exchange filing showed.  PetroEnergy Resources Corp. (PERC)   increased 1.7 percent
to 6 pesos, heading for the highest close since May 22. The
company will join exploration and drilling activities in West
Africa, the  Philippine (PASHR)  Star reported, citing Vice President
Francisco Delfin Jr. Delfin couldn’t be reached at his office
for comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
